                  <li>Would a million dollars be enough for retirement?</li>
                  <li>When can I retire?</li>
                  <li>How long will my retirement savings last?</li>
                  <li>How long will I live for?</li>
                  <li>How much more do I need to save?</li>
                </ul>
              </p>
              <p>
                It was far too complicated trying to answer those questions, so I simplified retirement planning down to a single question:
                <blockquote class="text-info"> How does my budget now compare to my retirement budget?  </blockquote>
                Once you make this comparison, everything else falls into place.  Basically, you will know whether or not you can maintain your current lifestyle through retirement.
                So, I created this calculator to answer that question, and I hope you find it useful.
              </p>
