                  <p>
                    Most American workers will receive social security benefits in retirement.  Social Security is a safety net to ensure that retired Americans do not live in poverty.
                    Your social security benefit varies depending on your income, how long you have worked and when you start collecting social security.  
                  </p>
                  <p>
