                  <h2>Return on Investment </h2>
                  <p class="h3"><small>In any investment, you expect to have fun and make money.  -Michael Jordan</small></p>
                  <p>
                    Your savings should be invested so that it can grow as quickly as possible without too much risk.  Historically, the stock market provides an average return on investment 
                    (<a href="http://www.investopedia.com/terms/r/returnoninvestment.asp" target="_blank">ROI</a>) of  
                    <a href="http://www.thesimpledollar.com/where-does-7-come-from-when-it-comes-to-long-term-stock-returns/" target="_blank">7%</a><sup>1, 2</sup> each year over the long term.
                  </p>
                  <p>
                    Select the type of investment most applicable to your retirement savings:
                  </p>
                  <div id="investmentOptions" class="subtable">
                    <div class="radio">
                      <input name="investmentType" type="radio" value="1.0">
